- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is relevant as the paper discusses approximation techniques for computing centrality measures in large-scale networks.
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is relevant as the paper uses neural network learning algorithms to approximate centrality measures.
